1. Qb3+ Ka1 2. Qd1+ Kb2 3. Qd2+ Kb1 4. Kd3!? { Using the second of two winning squares available for White's king - c2. } (4. Kc3 a1=Q+ 5. Kb3 { was the mating motif covered in the last example - with 4.Kd3 we see the other idea, that being the mate on c2. }) 4... a1=N (4... a1=Q 5. Qc2#) 5. Kc3 $18 *


