{ Here White has a larger winning zone (+2 files from the rook pawn, if that's easy to remember) because both the standard mate by Kb3 and a Qe2# mate option are possible. This is only the case because Black's king is on the longer side. } { [%csl Ga5,Gb5,Gc5,Gd5,Gd4,Ge4,Gf4,Gg4,Gg3,Gg2,Gg1,Yb3,Yf3,Yf2,Yf1] }
1. Qd4+ Ke2 (1... Kc1 2. Kb4 Kb1 3. Qd3 Kb2 4. Qd2 Kb1 5. Kb3 $18) 2. Qc3 Kd1 3. Qd3+ Kc1 4. Kb4 Kb2 5. Qd2 Kb1 6. Kb3 $18 c1=Q (6... c1=N+ 7. Ka3 $18) 7. Qa2# *


