{ When the king is already on the short side, as is the case here, White can only win by either the standard mate with Kb3 (this time he only has one move to get there) or by blockading the c1-square via Kd2. With the king on a4 White can only win via the former plan. } { [%csl Ga4,Gb4,Gc4,Gc3,Gd3,Ge3,Ge2,Ge1,Yb3,Yd2] }
1. Qb4+ Ka2 2. Qd2 (2. Qc3?? c1=Q! 3. Qxc1 $10) 2... Kb1 3. Kb3 $18 *


